author: David Gura
title: Jobless claims reach 26 million since coronavirus hit, wiping out all gains since 2008 recession
description: Jobless claims reach 26 million since coronavirus hit, wiping out all gains since 2008 recession
content:
Another 4.4 million Americans filed for initial jobless claims last week, revealing that at least 26 million people have requested unemployment benefits since the outbreak of the coronavirus pandemic.
